result.adr_address: 11 Davis St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 11 Davis St, Kennedy Town, Hong Kong
result.name: Maison Eric Kayser - Kennedy Town

reviews.text: Very bad attitude of the store manager and the barista. Very poor quality coffee. Croissant quality is also low, even worse than a normal local Hong Kong bakery. Very contradictory to the claimed "paris" brand.

Just came across this place tonight for the first time.  Liked the look of the raspberry item.  As I was reminded once again, looks can be deceiving.  As far as I know, there is no good Western bakery item in HK, and this is no exception.  Not authentic and at 30HKD extremely and unnecessarily expensive.  I will continue instead to go to my local, family-run HK-style bakery in Mong Kok, where I get the best baked items for between 4.5 and 12 HKD each.  Bad taste and not worth the price.

Great place based on their primary product which is their bread and bakery. Sandwiches are well priced, fresh and tasty. Their bread is as good as it gets in HK. I havent tried their coffee or other products. Staff are always friendly too which is a welcome change!

Good coffee and tea choices. Soya milk is available. Breads and pastries are well-marked with allergens, so it's easy to find vegan products. They sell freshly made sandwiches too, but none are vegan.

Bread is well-made. Their pastries and sandwich are good. Coffee is piping hot and aromatic. Service can definitely  be improved. A smile will go a long way. One of their staff is almost screaming at their customers when announcing their orders. It ruins your Sunday morning experience.
